elect name=year><option value=2004>2004</option><option value=2005>2005</option><option value=2006 selected>2006</option></select> <input type=submit value=Go></form><p><TABLE WIDTH="94%" BORDER=0 CELLPADDING=0 CELLSPACING=0><TR><TD><IMG SRC="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/dateheader_01.gif"></TD><TD WIDTH="100%" background="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/dateheader_02.gif"><span CLASS="newsdate">Sat 02 Sep 2006</span></TD><TD><IMG SRC="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/dateheader_03.gif"></TD></TR></TABLE><br><!-------Start News item--><table cellSpacing=0 cellPadding=0 width="94%" border=0>             <tr>           <td width=23><img src="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/newsbox_01.jpg"></td>           <td  width=100%        background="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/newsbox_02.jpg"></td>           <td><img         src="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/newsbox_03.jpg"></td></tr>         <tr>           <td           background="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/newsbox_04.jpg" width="17px">&nbsp;</td>           <td             background="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/newsbox_05.jpg"><a name="20838"></a><span CLASS="newstitle">'Resurrecting EverQuest' Article</span><br><span class="feat"><a href="http://vnboards.ign.com/forums/b1/98742352">[Post A Comment]</a> - <a href=pagetools/pagetools.php?act=printnews&id=20838>Print News</a> | <a href="?dir=pagetools&content=mailnews&id=20838">Mail News</a></span><br>Does EverQuest need a rez?  Slashdot.com's Michael Zenke has gone from "frustration and disappointment" with EQ to "I've seen the light."<br><br>After taking a tour with Rashere around the new expansion, his <a href="http://www.gametab.com/news/666320/">article</a> refers to the TSS expansion as "nothing less that a relaunch of EverQuest" and "EverQuest 1.5."<br><br>The main point of his article is that TSS is targeting players that subscribed in the past and will want to return given the content being released in just a couple of weeks.  Rather than focusing on a lot of new features for the game, they've concentrated on "focusing on the players," according to Zenke.  "SOE hopes that, by providing a clear quest path incorporating all of the innovations and upgrades the game has received since launch, players will be able to experience the best of what EQ has to offer," he explains.<br><br>I agree that TSS is a great idea, giving players another Kunark-type expansion, plus some time saving features and a new race to have fun with.  However, Zenke's comment, "SOE seems finally to have come around to the idea that they should be spending time and effort on the players," seems gratutious at best, since as an eight year veteran I have seen the SOE Team focus on the players since the game was launched, probably more than any other MMO out there.  The SOE Development Team has always listened to the players, steadily improving EQ and making it better every day.  But, if this new expansion brings back old players from where ever they wandered off to, that's fantastic.  The Progression server began the process, but a new player-oriented expansion on the current servers is even better.<br><br>If anyone can deliver "a love letter to the players," as Zenke puts it, it's the current SOE development team.  In my opinion, TSS is just another dozen roses in the on-going romance.<br><br><br><span CLASS="newsby">-- <a href="/siteinfo/mail.php?staff=Kwill">Kwill</a> @ Sat 02 Sep 2006</span><br><br><br><img src="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/spacer.gif" width="540px" height=1></td>           <td           background="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/newsbox_06.jpg" width="17px">&nbsp;</td></tr>         <tr>           <td width=23><img src="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/newsbox_07.jpg"></td>           <td           background="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/newsbox_08.jpg"></td>           <td><img         src="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/newsbox_09.jpg"></td></tr></table></p><!-------End News item--><p><TABLE WIDTH="94%" BORDER=0 CELLPADDING=0 CELLSPACING=0><TR><TD><IMG SRC="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/dateheader_01.gif"></TD><TD WIDTH="100%" background="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/dateheader_02.gif"><span CLASS="newsdate">Thu 31 Aug 2006</span></TD><TD><IMG SRC="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/dateheader_03.gif"></TD></TR></TABLE><br><!-------Start News item--><table cellSpacing=0 cellPadding=0 width="94%" border=0>             <tr>           <td width=23><img src="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/newsbox_01.jpg"></td>           <td  width=100%        background="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/newsbox_02.jpg"></td>           <td><img         src="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/newsbox_03.jpg"></td></tr>         <tr>           <td           background="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/newsbox_04.jpg" width="17px">&nbsp;</td>           <td             background="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/newsbox_05.jpg"><a name="20781"></a><span CLASS="newstitle">Female Drakkin Screenshots</span><br><span class="feat"><a href="http://vnboards.ign.com/forums/b1/98709436">[Post A Comment]</a> - <a href=pagetools/pagetools.php?act=printnews&id=20781>Print News</a> | <a href="?dir=pagetools&content=mailnews&id=20781">Mail News</a></span><br>The female version of the newest player race, the Drakkin, has been released as screenshots.  They are kind of willowy, aren't they?  Drakkin females are little different from some of the previous female character models we've seen.<br><br><a href="http://eqvault.ign.com/screenshots/image.php?ss=661"><br><img src="http://eqvault.ign.com/screenshots/thumb.php?ss=661"</a><br><br><a href="http://eqvault.ign.com/screenshots/image.php?ss=662"><br><img src="http://eqvault.ign.com/screenshots/thumb.php?ss=662"</a><br><br><a href="http://eqvault.ign.com/screenshots/image.php?ss=663"><br><img src="http://eqvault.ign.com/screenshots/thumb.php?ss=663"</a><br><br><span CLASS="newsby">-- <a href="/siteinfo/mail.php?staff=Kwill">Kwill</a> @ Thu 31 Aug 2006</span><br><br><br><img src="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/spacer.gif" width="540px" height=1></td>           <td           background="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/newsbox_06.jpg" width="17px">&nbsp;</td></tr>         <tr>           <td width=23><img src="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/newsbox_07.jpg"></td>           <td           background="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/newsbox_08.jpg"></td>           <td><img         src="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/newsbox_09.jpg"></td></tr></table></p><!-------End News item--><p><TABLE WIDTH="94%" BORDER=0 CELLPADDING=0 CELLSPACING=0><TR><TD><IMG SRC="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/dateheader_01.gif"></TD><TD WIDTH="100%" background="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/dateheader_02.gif"><span CLASS="newsdate">Tue 29 Aug 2006</span></TD><TD><IMG SRC="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/dateheader_03.gif"></TD></TR></TABLE><br><!-------Start News item--><table cellSpacing=0 cellPadding=0 width="94%" border=0>             <tr>           <td width=23><img src="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/newsbox_01.jpg"></td>           <td  width=100%        background="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/newsbox_02.jpg"></td>           <td><img         src="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/newsbox_03.jpg"></td></tr>         <tr>           <td           background="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/newsbox_04.jpg" width="17px">&nbsp;</td>           <td             background="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/newsbox_05.jpg"><a name="20707"></a><span CLASS="newstitle">Rashere on General Upcoming Changes</span><br><span class="feat"><a href="http://vnboards.ign.com/forums/b1/98672423">[Post A Comment]</a> - <a href=pagetools/pagetools.php?act=printnews&id=20707>Print News</a> | <a href="?dir=pagetools&content=mailnews&id=20707">Mail News</a></span><br>Rashere has announced a number of upcoming changes to the game:<br><br><strong>AA</strong><br>We’re moving the AA system to a more relative system so the amount of AA experience you gain will be based on the difficulty (con level) of the NPC you killed rather than its level (quest XP and other ways of getting AA are likewise converted over to the new system).<br><br><strong>Spell Resists</strong><br>We’ll be introducing a new spell resist formula that will make spell resists much more lenient than they have been in the past.<br><br><strong>Death</strong><br>We’ll be changing death so that when you die, you will be “hovering” over your body and can choose to stay that way while waiting for a resurrection instead of immediately zoning to your bind point.  This is being done to help players on slow connections who take a big hit from having to zone twice when they die. <br><br><strong>Character Creation</strong><br>We’ve changed character creation to make it more graphical, allow characters to be created from a single page, and update it to include features associated with the new Drakkin race.<br><br><strong>Endless Quiver</strong><br>We’ve introduced the ability to create new arrows that are not affected by Endless Quiver.  These arrows will specifically be marked as “Expendable”. <br><br><br><br><p><a href="fullstory.php?id=20707">Read More...</a><br><br><span CLASS="newsby">-- <a href="/siteinfo/mail.php?staff=Kwill">Kwill</a> @ Tue 29 Aug 2006</span><br><br><br><a name="20704"></a><span CLASS="newstitle">Rashere on Upcoming Downtime Changes</span><br><span class="feat"><a href="http://vnboards.ign.com/forums/b1/98672255">[Post A Comment]</a> - <a href=pagetools/pagetools.php?act=printnews&id=20704>Print News</a> | <a href="?dir=pagetools&content=mailnews&id=20704">Mail News</a></span><br>Along with the new expansion to be released in September, the design team is working on some fundamental changes in the combat/non-combat states, which may or may not be pushed live when the expansion is.  The basic idea is to reduce the amount of downtime in EQ.  Read below for all the details, but here is the executive summary courtest of Rashere as posted on EQPlayers:<br><br>"Once you have been out-of-combat for a sufficient amount of time, you can sit down (or be on a non-moving horse) and begin to rest.  While resting, you enter an accelerated regeneration state that will quickly recover your mana, health, and endurance.  For most single group content, once you are out of combat for 30 seconds you can rest.  While dealing with multi-group content, that time is 5 minutes. <br><br>There are a series of icons that will display by your character’s name to let you know what your character’s current state is.<br><br>Crossed Swords – You are currently in-combat.<br><br>Hour Glass – You are out of combat, but not yet in a resting state.  In addition to the hourglass, there is a timer bar beneath the endurance bar that will count down as you get closer to being rested.<br><br>Poison Drop – You are no longer in combat, but cannot rest because of a debuff that is affecting you.  You must get rid of the debuff before you can rest.<br><br>Void – The void is the default icon and indicates that you are not in-combat and you can rest at any time.<br><br>Energy Swirl – The energy swirl indicates that you are currently resting."<br><br>It seems that these changes are partly to address the endurance regeneration problems, as well as mana regen for the large pools of mana at the higher levels.<p><a href="fullstory.php?id=20704">Read More...</a><br><br><span CLASS="newsby">-- <a href="/siteinfo/mail.php?staff=Kwill">Kwill</a> @ Tue 29 Aug 2006</span><br><br><br><a name="20702"></a><span CLASS="newstitle">Woes of the Non-Raiding Player</span><br><span class="feat"><a href="http://vnboards.ign.com/forums/b1/98671100">[Post A Comment]</a> - <a href=pagetools/pagetools.php?act=printnews&id=20702>Print News</a> | <a href="?dir=pagetools&content=mailnews&id=20702">Mail News</a></span><br>Loral, who runs <a href="http://www.mobhunter.com">Mobhunter</a>, an excellent EQ site, has posted a <a href="http://www.mobhunter.com/001495.html">provacative video</a> entitled "Prophecy of Ro Single Group Progression Video."   The video is very pointed statement by Loral in direct rebuttal to the Township Rebellion video of the submission of Deathknell, and expresses his position on the lack of ability to find groups in the newest expansion.<br><br>Loral is a level 70 cleric, a self-proclaimed "non-raider."  His commentaries on the lack of equivalent gear and opportunities for players who do not raid with a guild have been an important counterpoint to the raiding emphasis in the current game environment. For the non-raider to succeed, pickup groups are paramount to the game experience.  His video makes a poignant statement about the difficulty in finding a group to play with if you are not raiding.<br><br>Loral comments, "Pickup groups are a very important part of the game. Not everyone can rely on a tight knit group of friends with the right classes, right levels, right equipment power, and right time frames to meet these challenges. WOW solves this with solo content but at the expense of good group dynamics. EQ can do better."<br><br>Without the ability to easily form groups when any individual logs on, the game fabric indeed will unravel.  Two, three, and four boxing is not the answer to conquering group content to ensure character progression.  The fun of EQ is in meeting and playing with other people.  If the game is to attract and retain players, there have to be opportunities outside the raiding environment for people to enjoy the content.  One type of play style is not enough.<br><br>But is this now a non-issue? Frodlin, the warrior community representative, a member of a top raiding guild, and a self-proclaimed "SOE cheerleeder,"  <a href="http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=Veterans&message.id=275100&view=by_date_ascending&page=1">comments</a> on the EQPlayers board:<br><br>"[Loral's] biggest problem is that he got everything he asked for, and is now a crusader without a crusade.   PoR was unequivocally THE least raider friendly, and THE most casual friendly expansion ever released outside of Legacy of Ykesha, he got his chance to deprive raiders of a good time, while enjoying everything he claimed to be asking for:  A method to get Qvic level armor without organized raiding, entire zones devoted to casual grouping and easy to finish quests for gear that are significantly easier and represent a no-brainer to receive in relation to the same stuff a couple expansions ago, and no group content which benefits raiders in any way.  It was the perfect expansion if you listened to what Loral wanted... and it resulted in what he got, which is the LFG movie.<br><br>One day, perhaps he'll learn that challenge is what drives people, and not "catering to the bottom".  Until then, we'll see more and more of these silly antics like the rallying of the troops because of 2 hard zones, and the "LFG because I got everything I wanted in an expansion" movies."<br><br>The best we can say is that PoR may be the most "casual friendly" according to the raiding crowd, but if the zones are empty, there's a larger problem than the design of the zones themselves.<br><br>Is creating content that is not raid oriented "catering to the bottom" as Frodlin would like us to believe? Has the creation of a large amount of single group content that does not require a raid force solved the problem of lack of opportunities and gear for the non-raider?  Many players now feel without a doubt that this issue is yesterday's news, and the issues that Loral has raised are no longer valid.  Others would say that the video does express their frustration with getting a group.<br><br>EverQuest's design and sheer size has created a huge universe of play style opportunties, much more than any other game in this genre.  It is probably inevitable that the debate over content emphasis between the non-raider and the raider will go on as long as the game keeps growing.<br><br>Whatever side you fall on in this debate, kudos to Loral and Frodlin, as well as others, for posting opinions and talking about this very important fundamental issue of game design -- the way people play the game.  This debate means we are all better informed and can form our own opinions on whether there is enough content for how each of us want to play the game.<br><br><span CLASS="newsby">-- <a href="/siteinfo/mail.php?staff=Kwill">Kwill</a> @ Tue 29 Aug 2006</span><br><br><br><a name="20701"></a><span CLASS="newstitle">Third SOE Podcast</span><br><span class="feat"><a href="http://vnboards.ign.com/forums/b1/98669487">[Post A Comment]</a> - <a href=pagetools/pagetools.php?act=printnews&id=20701>Print News</a> | <a href="?dir=pagetools&content=mailnews&id=20701">Mail News</a></span><br>Andy Sites is the guest of Brenlo and Blackguard for the <a href="http://eqplayers.station.sony.com/news_article.vm?id=50223">third podcast from SOE.</a>  Andy Sites is the producer of the new PSP title, "Untold Legends."<br><br><span CLASS="newsby">-- <a href="/siteinfo/mail.php?staff=Kwill">Kwill</a> @ Tue 29 Aug 2006</span><br><br><br><img src="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/spacer.gif" width="540px" height=1></td>           <td           background="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/newsbox_06.jpg" width="17px">&nbsp;</td></tr>         <tr>           <td width=23><img src="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/newsbox_07.jpg"></td>           <td           background="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/newsbox_08.jpg"></td>           <td><img         src="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/newsbox_09.jpg"></td></tr></table></p><!-------End News item--></center>
</td></tr></table></DIV>
